          <h1 className="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold font-serif mb-2">
            Intertextuality Collation Machine <span className="text-academic-gold font-light">(ICoMa)</span>
          </h1>
          <p className="text-sm text-gray-300 font-mono">
            Experimental Version | ISO/IEC 10646:2017 Compliant
          </p>
        </div>
      </header>

      <main className="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-8">

        {/* Abstract */}
        <section className="bg-academic-paper border-l-4 border-academic-gold p-6 mb-8 text-sm leading-relaxed shadow-sm">
          <strong className="text-academic-gold block mb-2 uppercase tracking-wide">Abstract</strong>
          This digital instrument implements computational algorithms for the detection and analysis of textual parallels across manuscript witnesses. The system supports Unicode blocks for Coptic, Greek, Latin, CJK, and Indic scripts, employing n-gram analysis, normalized edit distance, Smith-Waterman local alignment, and newly integrated Passim/TRACER style methodologies.
        </section>

        {/* Controls */}
        <div className="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-12 gap-8">

          {/* Inputs */}
          <div className="lg:col-span-8 space-y-6">
            <div className="flex flex-col md:flex-row justify-between items-start md:items-end mb-4 border-b-2 border-academic-gold pb-2 gap-4">
              <h2 className="text-lg font-bold shrink-0">
                <span className="text-academic-gold mr-2">1.</span>Data Input
              </h2>
              <div className="flex flex-wrap gap-2 justify-end">
                {Object.entries(EXAMPLES).map(([key, val]) => (
                  <button
                    key={key}
                    onClick={() => { setSourceText(val.a); setTargetText(val.b); }}
                    className="text-xs px-3 py-1 bg-white border border-gray-300 hover:bg-academic-blue hover:text-white transition-colors uppercase font-mono rounded-sm whitespace-nowrap"
